ter when they broke into her home to check on her.\", \"from\": 252, \"to\": 373, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Police officers\", \"from\": 252, \"to\": 267}, {\"ngram\": \"the 50-year-old's lifeless body\", \"from\": 279, \"to\": 310}, {\"ngram\": \"her home\", \"from\": 348, \"to\": 356}]}, {\"sentence\": \"An autopsy carried out by state authorities in Nevada found solid food remains lodged in Larreal's windpipe and is thought to have died of asphyxiation.\", \"from\": 375, \"to\": 527, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 422, \"end\": 428, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nevada\", \"score\": 0.9996622792734153, \"rank\": 0.0003378348047738956, \"text\": \"Nevada\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nevada\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nevada\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"An autopsy\", \"from\": 375, \"to\": 385}, {\"ngram\": \"state authorities\", \"from\": 401, \"to\": 418}, {\"ngram\": \"Larreal's windpipe\", \"from\": 464, \"to\": 482}, {\"ngram\": \"asphyxiation\", \"from\": 514, \"to\": 526}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Investigations are still ongoing and her official cause of death has not yet been confirmed but Larreal is believed to have been dead since August 11.\", \"from\": 529, \"to\": 679, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Investigations\", \"from\": 529, \"to\": 543}, {\"ngram\": \"her official cause\", \"from\": 566, \"to\": 584}, {\"ngram\": \"death\", \"from\": 588, \"to\": 593}, {\"ngram\": \"Larreal\", \"from\": 625, \"to\": 632}, {\"ngram\": \"August\", \"from\": 669, \"to\": 675}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The track cyclist is one of Venezuela's most illustrious sports stars and is the nation's only athlete to have competed in five different Olympic Games between 1992 and 2012.\", \"from\": 681, \"to\": 855, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 709, \"end\": 718, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Venezuelan_presidential_crisis\", \"score\": 0.9665136988180258, \"rank\": 0.03464648351084879, \"text\": \"Venezuela\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Venezuelan_presidential_crisis\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Venezuelan_presidential_crisis\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The track cyclist\", \"from\": 681, \"to\": 698}, {\"ngram\": \"the nation's only athlete\", \"from\": 758, \"to\": 783}, {\"ngram\": \"five different Olympic Games\", \"from\": 804, \"to\": 832}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Despite never clinching a podium finish at the Olympics, Larreal was awarded four diplomas - a certificate handed to the top eight finishers in a competition at the Games.\", \"from\": 857, \"to\": 1028, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a podium finish\", \"from\": 881, \"to\": 896}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 900, \"to\": 912}, {\"ngram\": \"Larreal\", \"from\": 914, \"to\": 921}, {\"ngram\": \"four diplomas - a certificate\", \"from\": 934, \"to\": 963}, {\"ngram\": \"the top eight finishers\", \"from\": 974, \"to\": 997}, {\"ngram\": \"a competition\", \"from\": 1001, \"to\": 1014}, {\"ngram\": \"the Games\", \"from\": 1018, \"to\": 1027}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Larreal also won numerous gold medals during her career, including at the Pan American Games and South American Games.\", \"from\": 1030, \"to\": 1148, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1104, \"end\": 1122, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pan_American_Games\", \"score\": 0.9890407725372701, \"rank\": 0.00650000168100202, \"text\": \"Pan American Games\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pan_American_Games\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pan_American_Games\"}, {\"begin\": 1127, \"end\": 1147, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_American_Games\", \"score\": 0.9999999996775841, \"rank\": 3.2200103116673144e-10, \"text\": \"South American Games\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_American_Games\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_American_Games\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Larreal\", \"from\": 1030, \"to\": 1037}, {\"ngram\": \"numerous gold medals\", \"from\": 1047, \"to\": 1067}, {\"ngram\": \"her career\", \"from\": 1075, \"to\": 1085}]}, {\"sentence\": \"After London 2012, Larreal publicly opposed Venezuela's president Nicolas Maduro when he took over from Hugo Chaves and accused the new government's Ministry of Sports of corruption.\", \"from\": 1150, \"to\": 1332, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1150, \"end\": 1162, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Richard_Jefferies\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"After London\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Richard_Jefferies\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Richard_Jefferies\"}, {\"begin\": 1194, \"end\": 1203, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Venezuelan_presidential_crisis\", \"score\": 0.9665136988180258, \"rank\": 0.03464648351084879, \"text\": \"Venezuela\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Venezuelan_presidential_crisis\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Venezuelan_presidential_crisis\"}, {\"begin\": 1216, \"end\": 1230, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nicol\\u00e1s_Maduro\", \"score\": 0.9999999836136341, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Nicolas Maduro\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nicol\\u00e1s_Maduro\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nicol\\u00e1s_Maduro\"}, {\"begin\": 1259, \"end\": 1265, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/G.D._Chaves\", \"score\": 0.9999973879323543, \"rank\": 2.6120742810896438e-06, \"text\": \"Chaves\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/G.D._Chaves\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/G.D._Chaves\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Larreal\", \"from\": 1169, \"to\": 1176}, {\"ngram\": \"the new government's Ministry\", \"from\": 1278, \"to\": 1307}, {\"ngram\": \"Sports\", \"from\": 1311, \"to\": 1317}, {\"ngram\": \"corruption\", \"from\": 1321, \"to\": 1331}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She went on to become an activist who persistently stood up for 'freedom and democracy', effectively claiming Venezuela had become a dictatorship.\", \"from\": 1334, \"to\": 1480, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1444, \"end\": 1453, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Venezuelan_presidential_crisis\", \"score\": 0.9665136988180258, \"rank\": 0.03464648351084879, \"text\": \"Venezuela\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Venezuelan_presidential_crisis\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Venezuelan_presidential_crisis\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"an activist\", \"from\": 1356, \"to\": 1367}, {\"ngram\": \"freedom\", \"from\": 1399, \"to\": 1406}, {\"ngram\": \"democracy\", \"from\": 1411, \"to\": 1420}, {\"ngram\": \"a dictatorship\", \"from\": 1465, \"to\": 1479}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But Larreal's criticism of Maduro and the government led to her being subjected to death threats, so she fled her home country in exile and moved to the USA.\", \"from\": 1482, \"to\": 1639, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1635, \"end\": 1638, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999997291934417, \"rank\": 2.1413950594378938e-07, \"text\": \"USA\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Larreal's criticism\", \"from\": 1486, \"to\": 1505}, {\"ngram\": \"Maduro\", \"from\": 1509, \"to\": 1515}, {\"ngram\": \"the government\", \"from\": 1520, \"to\": 1534}, {\"ngram\": \"death threats\", \"from\": 1565, \"to\": 1578}, {\"ngram\": \"her home country\", \"from\": 1592, \"to\": 1608}, {\"ngram\": \"exile\", \"from\": 1612, \"to\": 1617}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It did not stop her from campaigning and even her last Instagram post on August 8 referenced the ongoing political unrest in Venezuela following Maduro's disputed victory in July's election.\", \"from\": 1641, \"to\": 1831, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1766, \"end\": 1775, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Venezuelan_presidential_crisis\", \"score\": 0.9665136988180258, \"rank\": 0.03464648351084879, \"text\": \"Venezuela\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Venezuelan_presidential_crisis\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Venezuelan_presidential_crisis\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"campaigning\", \"from\": 1666, \"to\": 1677}, {\"ngram\": \"even her last Instagram post\", \"from\": 1682, \"to\": 1710}, {\"ngram\": \"August\", \"from\": 1714, \"to\": 1720}, {\"ngram\": \"the ongoing political unrest\", \"from\": 1734, \"to\": 1762}, {\"ngram\": \"Maduro's disputed victory\", \"from\": 1786, \"to\": 1811}, {\"ngram\": \"July's election\", \"from\": 1815, \"to\": 1830}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Politician Henrique Capriles paid tribute to 'a great figure in cycling' and 'specialist in track events'.\", \"from\": 1833, \"to\": 1939, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1844, \"end\": 1861, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Henrique_Capriles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Henrique Capriles\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Henrique_Capriles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Henrique_Capriles\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"tribute\", \"from\": 1867, \"to\": 1874}, {\"ngram\": \"a great figure\", \"from\": 1879, \"to\": 1893}, {\"ngram\": \"cycling\", \"from\": 1897, \"to\": 1904}, {\"ngram\": \"'specialist\", \"from\": 1910, \"to\": 1921}, {\"ngram\": \"track events\", \"from\": 1925, \"to\": 1937}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He wrote on X: 'Daniela, in addition to winning medals, stood out for being the only Venezuelan to have participated in five Olympic Games.\", \"from\": 1941, \"to\": 2080, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 195